<subSubSection lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="24" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[498,1542,1060,1924]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Some studies (
<bibRefCitation author="Inoue H." box="[700,835,1060,1086]" journalOrPublisher="Insecta Japonica" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 106" part="4" refId="ref18985" refString="Inoue H. 1961. Lepidoptera: Geometridae. Insecta Japonica 4: 1 - 106." title="Lepidoptera: Geometridae" type="journal article" year="1961">
<emphasis box="[700,835,1060,1086]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Inoue, 1961</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Holloway J." box="[848,1027,1060,1086]" journalOrPublisher="Ennominae Malayan Nature Journal" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="147 - 326" part="49" refId="ref18919" refString="Holloway J. 1996. The moths of Borneo, part 9: Geometridae (incl. Orthostixini), Oenochrominae, Desmobathrinae, Geometrinae. Ennominae Malayan Nature Journal 49: 147 - 326." title="The moths of Borneo, part 9: Geometridae (incl. Orthostixini), Oenochrominae, Desmobathrinae, Geometrinae" type="journal article" year="1996">
<emphasis box="[848,1027,1060,1086]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Holloway, 1996</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
) suggested the morphological similarities of 
<taxonomicName authority="Warren, 1893" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1893" box="[498,863,1100,1127]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Chlorodontopera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[498,693,1100,1126]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Chlorodontopera</emphasis>
Warren, 1893
</taxonomicName>
with members of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Inoue" authorityYear="1961" box="[1081,1202,1100,1126]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Aracimini">Aracimini</taxonomicName>
. Moreover, 
<bibRefCitation author="Holloway J." box="[1343,1535,1100,1126]" journalOrPublisher="Ennominae Malayan Nature Journal" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="147 - 326" part="49" refId="ref18919" refString="Holloway J. 1996. The moths of Borneo, part 9: Geometridae (incl. Orthostixini), Oenochrominae, Desmobathrinae, Geometrinae. Ennominae Malayan Nature Journal 49: 147 - 326." title="The moths of Borneo, part 9: Geometridae (incl. Orthostixini), Oenochrominae, Desmobathrinae, Geometrinae" type="journal article" year="1996">
<emphasis box="[1343,1535,1100,1126]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Holloway (1996)</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
considered this genus as part of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Inoue" authorityYear="1961" box="[881,1002,1140,1166]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Aracimini">Aracimini</taxonomicName>
. Our results suggest a sister relationship of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1893" box="[498,693,1180,1206]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Chlorodontopera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[498,693,1180,1206]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Chlorodontopera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a large clade comprising 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Inoue" authorityYear="1961" box="[1058,1178,1180,1206]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Aracimini">Aracimini</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Inoue" authorityYear="1961" box="[1191,1377,1180,1206]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Neohipparchini">Neohipparchini</taxonomicName>
, Timandromorphini, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1829" box="[742,878,1220,1246]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Geometrini">Geometrini</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gumppenberg" authorityYear="1887" box="[891,1012,1220,1246]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Nemoriini">Nemoriini</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Inoue" authorityYear="1961" box="[1074,1228,1220,1246]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Comibaenini">Comibaenini</taxonomicName>
. Considering that our analysis strongly supports 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1893" box="[811,1006,1260,1286]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Chlorodontopera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[811,1006,1260,1286]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Chlorodontopera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as an independent lineage (branch support SH-like = 99 UFBoot2 = 100, RBS = 99), we introduce the monobasic tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Murillo-Ramos, Sihvonen &amp; Brehm" authorityYear="2019" box="[498,721,1339,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Chlorodontoperini">Chlorodontoperini</taxonomicName>
. This tribe can be diagnosed by the combination of DNA data from six genetic markers (exemplar 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[819,1156,1379,1405]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Chlorodontopera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discospilata">
<emphasis box="[819,1156,1379,1405]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Chlorodontopera discospilata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) CAD (MG015448), COI (MG014735), EF1a (MG015329), GAPDH (MG014862), MDH (MG014980) and RpS5 (MG015562). 
<bibRefCitation author="Ban X &amp; Jiang N &amp; Cheng R &amp; Xue D &amp; Han H." box="[664,859,1459,1485]" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="653 - 672" part="184" refId="ref18087" refString="Ban X, Jiang N, Cheng R, Xue D, Han H. 2018. Tribal classification and phylogeny of Geometrinae (Lepidoptera: Geometridae) inferred from seven gene regions. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 184 (3): 653 - 672 DOI 10.1093 / zoolinnean / zly 013." title="Tribal classification and phylogeny of Geometrinae (Lepidoptera: Geometridae) inferred from seven gene regions" type="journal article" year="2018">
<emphasis box="[664,859,1459,1485]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Ban et al. (2018)</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
did not introduce a new tribe because the relationship between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1893" box="[603,798,1499,1525]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Chlorodontopera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[603,798,1499,1525]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Chlorodontopera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Warren, 1896" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1896" box="[859,1116,1499,1525]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Euxena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[859,946,1500,1525]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Euxena</emphasis>
Warren, 1896
</taxonomicName>
was not clear in their study. This relationship was also been proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Holloway J." box="[969,1161,1539,1565]" journalOrPublisher="Ennominae Malayan Nature Journal" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="147 - 326" part="49" refId="ref18919" refString="Holloway J. 1996. The moths of Borneo, part 9: Geometridae (incl. Orthostixini), Oenochrominae, Desmobathrinae, Geometrinae. Ennominae Malayan Nature Journal 49: 147 - 326." title="The moths of Borneo, part 9: Geometridae (incl. Orthostixini), Oenochrominae, Desmobathrinae, Geometrinae" type="journal article" year="1996">
<emphasis box="[969,1161,1539,1565]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Holloway (1996)</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
based on similar wing patterns. Further analyses are needed to clarify the affinities between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1893" box="[1195,1390,1578,1604]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Chlorodontopera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1195,1390,1578,1604]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Chlorodontopera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1896" box="[1449,1536,1579,1604]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Euxena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1449,1536,1579,1604]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Euxena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[498,1542,1060,1924]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
The tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Murillo-Ramos, Sihvonen &amp; Brehm" authorityYear="2019" box="[644,857,1618,1644]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Chlorodontoperini">Chlorodontoperini</taxonomicName>
is diagnosed by distinct discal spots with pale margins on the wings, which are larger on the hindwing; a dull reddish-brown patch is present between the discal spot and the costa on the hindwing, and veins M3 and CuA1 are not stalked on the hindwing (
<bibRefCitation author="Ban X &amp; Jiang N &amp; Cheng R &amp; Xue D &amp; Han H." box="[706,883,1738,1764]" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="653 - 672" part="184" refId="ref18087" refString="Ban X, Jiang N, Cheng R, Xue D, Han H. 2018. Tribal classification and phylogeny of Geometrinae (Lepidoptera: Geometridae) inferred from seven gene regions. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 184 (3): 653 - 672 DOI 10.1093 / zoolinnean / zly 013." title="Tribal classification and phylogeny of Geometrinae (Lepidoptera: Geometridae) inferred from seven gene regions" type="journal article" year="2018">
<emphasis box="[706,883,1738,1764]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Ban et al., 2018</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
). In the male genitalia, the socii are stout and setose and the lateral arms of the gnathos are developed, not joined. Sternite 3 of the male has setal patches (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Holloway J." box="[638,810,1817,1844]" journalOrPublisher="Ennominae Malayan Nature Journal" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="147 - 326" part="49" refId="ref18919" refString="Holloway J. 1996. The moths of Borneo, part 9: Geometridae (incl. Orthostixini), Oenochrominae, Desmobathrinae, Geometrinae. Ennominae Malayan Nature Journal 49: 147 - 326." title="The moths of Borneo, part 9: Geometridae (incl. Orthostixini), Oenochrominae, Desmobathrinae, Geometrinae" type="journal article" year="1996">
<emphasis box="[638,810,1817,1844]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Holloway, 1996</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
for illustrations). Formal taxonomic changesare listedin 
<tableCitation box="[1453,1535,1818,1844]" captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="15.[117,172,248,269]" captionText="Table 2 Summary of formally proposed taxonomic changes." pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Table 2</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[498,1542,1060,1924]" lastBlockId="23.[498,1542,234,1018]" lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="24" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Inoue" authorityYear="1961" box="[530,650,1857,1883]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Aracimini">Aracimini</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Inoue" authorityYear="1961" box="[663,849,1857,1883]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Neohipparchini">Neohipparchini</taxonomicName>
, Timandromorphini, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1829" box="[1107,1241,1857,1883]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Geometrini">Geometrini</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Inoue" authorityYear="1961" box="[1302,1453,1857,1883]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Comibaenini">Comibaenini</taxonomicName>
were recovered as monophyletic groups. These results are in full agreement with 
<bibRefCitation author="Ban X &amp; Jiang N &amp; Cheng R &amp; Xue D &amp; Han H." box="[498,693,234,260]" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="653 - 672" part="184" refId="ref18087" refString="Ban X, Jiang N, Cheng R, Xue D, Han H. 2018. Tribal classification and phylogeny of Geometrinae (Lepidoptera: Geometridae) inferred from seven gene regions. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 184 (3): 653 - 672 DOI 10.1093 / zoolinnean / zly 013." title="Tribal classification and phylogeny of Geometrinae (Lepidoptera: Geometridae) inferred from seven gene regions" type="journal article" year="2018">
<emphasis box="[498,693,234,260]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Ban et al. (2018)</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
. However, the phylogenetic position of 
<taxonomicName authority="Warren, 1894" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1894" box="[1166,1459,234,261]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Eucyclodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1166,1289,234,260]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Eucyclodes</emphasis>
Warren, 1894
</taxonomicName>
is uncertain (unnamed G2). The monophyly of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gumppenberg" authorityYear="1887" box="[1026,1147,274,300]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Nemoriini">Nemoriini</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferguson" authorityYear="1969" box="[1205,1339,274,300]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Synchlorini">Synchlorini</taxonomicName>
is not supported. Instead, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferguson" authorityYear="1969" box="[599,733,314,340]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Synchlorini">Synchlorini</taxonomicName>
are nested within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gumppenberg" authorityYear="1887" box="[953,1074,314,340]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Nemoriini">Nemoriini</taxonomicName>
(support branch SH-like = 98.3, UFBoot2 = 91, RBS = 93). Our findings are in concordance with 
<bibRefCitation author="Sihvonen P &amp; Mutanen M &amp; Kaila L &amp; Brehm G &amp; Hausmann A &amp; Staude HS" box="[1244,1491,354,380]" journalOrPublisher="PLOS ONE" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="20356" part="6" refId="ref20700" refString="Sihvonen P, Mutanen M, Kaila L, Brehm G, Hausmann A, Staude HS. 2011. Comprehensive molecular sampling yields a robust phylogeny for geometrid moths (Lepidoptera: Geometridae). PLOS ONE 6 (6): e 20356 DOI 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0020356." title="Comprehensive molecular sampling yields a robust phylogeny for geometrid moths (Lepidoptera: Geometridae)" type="journal article" year="2011">
<emphasis box="[1244,1491,354,380]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicName authority="Murillo-Ramos &amp; Brehm &amp; Sihvonen &amp; Hausmann &amp; Holm &amp; Ghanavi &amp; Õunap &amp; Truuverk &amp; Staude &amp; Friedrich &amp; Tammaru &amp; Wahlberg, 2019" authorityName="Murillo-Ramos &amp; Brehm &amp; Sihvonen &amp; Hausmann &amp; Holm &amp; Ghanavi &amp; Õunap &amp; Truuverk &amp; Staude &amp; Friedrich &amp; Tammaru &amp; Wahlberg" authorityYear="2019" box="[1244,1349,354,380]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" status="new subfamily" subFamily="Sihvonen">Sihvonen</taxonomicName>
et al. (2011)
</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Ban X &amp; Jiang N &amp; Cheng R &amp; Xue D &amp; Han H." box="[498,687,394,420]" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="653 - 672" part="184" refId="ref18087" refString="Ban X, Jiang N, Cheng R, Xue D, Han H. 2018. Tribal classification and phylogeny of Geometrinae (Lepidoptera: Geometridae) inferred from seven gene regions. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 184 (3): 653 - 672 DOI 10.1093 / zoolinnean / zly 013." title="Tribal classification and phylogeny of Geometrinae (Lepidoptera: Geometridae) inferred from seven gene regions" type="journal article" year="2018">
<emphasis box="[498,687,394,420]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Ban et al. (2018)</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
, but our analyses included a larger number of markers and a much higher number of taxa. Thus, we formally synonymize 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferguson" authorityYear="1969" box="[1064,1198,433,459]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" status="syn. nov." tribe="Synchlorini">Synchlorini</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1207,1316,434,460]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1207,1316,434,460]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">syn. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gumppenberg" authorityYear="1887" box="[1386,1507,433,459]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Nemoriini">Nemoriini</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation box="[508,596,473,499]" captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="15.[117,172,248,269]" captionText="Table 2 Summary of formally proposed taxonomic changes." pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[498,1542,234,1018]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
The monophyly of 
<taxonomicName authority="sensu Pitkin, Han &amp; James (2007)" authorityName="sensu Pitkin, Han &amp; James" authorityYear="2007" box="[759,1343,513,540]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Pseudoterpnini">
Pseudoterpnini 
<emphasis box="[945,1343,513,540]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Pitkin LM &amp; Han HX &amp; James S." box="[1016,1343,513,540]" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="343 - 412" part="150" refId="ref20030" refString="Pitkin LM, Han HX, James S. 2007. Moths of the tribe Pseudoterpnini (Geometridae: Geometrinae): a review of the genera. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 150 (2): 343 - 412 DOI 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.2007.00287. x." title="Moths of the tribe Pseudoterpnini (Geometridae: Geometrinae): a review of the genera" type="journal article" year="2007">Pitkin, Han &amp; James (2007)</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could not be recovered. Similar results were shown by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ban X &amp; Jiang N &amp; Cheng R &amp; Xue D &amp; Han H." box="[984,1177,553,579]" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="653 - 672" part="184" refId="ref18087" refString="Ban X, Jiang N, Cheng R, Xue D, Han H. 2018. Tribal classification and phylogeny of Geometrinae (Lepidoptera: Geometridae) inferred from seven gene regions. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 184 (3): 653 - 672 DOI 10.1093 / zoolinnean / zly 013." title="Tribal classification and phylogeny of Geometrinae (Lepidoptera: Geometridae) inferred from seven gene regions" type="journal article" year="2018">
<emphasis box="[984,1177,553,579]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Ban et al. (2018)</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
who recovered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Pitkin, Han &amp; James" authorityYear="2007" box="[1364,1542,553,579]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Pseudoterpnini">Pseudoterpnini</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[498,522,593,619]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">s.l</emphasis>
. including all the genera previously studied by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pitkin LM &amp; Han HX &amp; James S." box="[1082,1409,593,619]" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="343 - 412" part="150" refId="ref20030" refString="Pitkin LM, Han HX, James S. 2007. Moths of the tribe Pseudoterpnini (Geometridae: Geometrinae): a review of the genera. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 150 (2): 343 - 412 DOI 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.2007.00287. x." title="Moths of the tribe Pseudoterpnini (Geometridae: Geometrinae): a review of the genera" type="journal article" year="2007">
<emphasis box="[1082,1409,593,619]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Pitkin, Han &amp; James (2007)</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
, forming a separate clade from 
<taxonomicName authority="Hubner, 1823" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1823" box="[737,1063,633,659]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Pseudoterpna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[737,893,633,659]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Pseudoterpna</emphasis>
Hübner, 1823
</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName authority="Moore, 1887" authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1887" box="[1098,1348,633,659]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Pingasa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1098,1188,633,658]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Pingasa</emphasis>
Moore, 1887
</taxonomicName>
. Our results showed African 
<taxonomicName authority="Prout, 1922" authorityName="Prout" authorityYear="1922" box="[691,988,673,699]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Mictoschema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[691,842,673,699]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Mictoschema</emphasis>
Prout, 1922
</taxonomicName>
falling within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Pitkin, Han &amp; James" authorityYear="2007" box="[1162,1340,673,699]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Pseudoterpnini">Pseudoterpnini</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[1349,1394,673,698]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">s.str</emphasis>
., and it is sister to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1823" box="[595,751,712,738]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Pseudoterpna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[595,751,712,738]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Pseudoterpna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1887" box="[808,898,713,738]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Pingasa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[808,898,713,738]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Pingasa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Asecond group of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Pitkin, Han &amp; James" authorityYear="2007" box="[1129,1307,712,738]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Pseudoterpnini">Pseudoterpnini</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[1313,1336,712,738]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">s.l</emphasis>
. was recovered as an independent lineage clearly separate from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Pitkin, Han &amp; James" authorityYear="2007" box="[1035,1213,752,778]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Pseudoterpnini">Pseudoterpnini</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[1222,1267,753,778]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">s.str</emphasis>
. (SH-like = 88.3, UFBoot2 = 64). 
<bibRefCitation author="Ban X &amp; Jiang N &amp; Cheng R &amp; Xue D &amp; Han H." box="[690,883,792,818]" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="653 - 672" part="184" refId="ref18087" refString="Ban X, Jiang N, Cheng R, Xue D, Han H. 2018. Tribal classification and phylogeny of Geometrinae (Lepidoptera: Geometridae) inferred from seven gene regions. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 184 (3): 653 - 672 DOI 10.1093 / zoolinnean / zly 013." title="Tribal classification and phylogeny of Geometrinae (Lepidoptera: Geometridae) inferred from seven gene regions" type="journal article" year="2018">
<emphasis box="[690,883,792,818]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Ban et al. (2018)</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
did not introduce a new tribe due to the morphological similarities and difficulty in finding apomorphies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Pitkin, Han &amp; James" authorityYear="2007" box="[1101,1279,832,858]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Pseudoterpnini">Pseudoterpnini</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[1286,1331,833,858]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">s.str</emphasis>
. In addition, their results were weakly supported. Considering that two independent studies have demonstrated the paraphyly of 
<taxonomicName authority="sensu Pitkin et al. (2007)" authorityName="sensu Pitkin et al." authorityYear="2007" box="[863,1335,912,938]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Pseudoterpnini">
Pseudoterpnini 
<emphasis box="[1048,1110,912,937]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pitkin LM &amp; Han HX &amp; James S." box="[1117,1335,912,938]" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="343 - 412" part="150" refId="ref20030" refString="Pitkin LM, Han HX, James S. 2007. Moths of the tribe Pseudoterpnini (Geometridae: Geometrinae): a review of the genera. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 150 (2): 343 - 412 DOI 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.2007.00287. x." title="Moths of the tribe Pseudoterpnini (Geometridae: Geometrinae): a review of the genera" type="journal article" year="2007">Pitkin et al. (2007)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, we see no reason for retaining the wide concept of this tribe. Instead, we propose the revival of the tribe status of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viidalepp" authorityYear="1981" box="[606,787,991,1017]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Archaeobalbini">Archaeobalbini</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
